00:04:45.920 --> 00:04:47.521
so kind of one person could build a

00:04:47.540 --> 00:04:49.362
stable protocol another person could build

00:04:49.822 --> 00:04:51.483
an oracle the third person could build a

00:04:51.524 --> 00:04:54.105
lending market and the fourth person could

00:04:54.125 --> 00:04:56.026
build a prediction market and somehow kind

00:04:56.045 --> 00:04:57.646
of like all of these could plug into

00:04:57.706 --> 00:05:00.189
each other seamlessly and without actually

00:05:00.209 --> 00:05:03.130
having to ask for permission and um

00:05:03.591 --> 00:05:05.451
without having to have

00:05:05.836 --> 00:05:08.557
this pre-planned in some way.

00:05:10.218 --> 00:05:11.958
This is also why we chose the Lego

00:05:11.978 --> 00:05:13.238
blocks for the video.

00:05:14.259 --> 00:05:18.321
This is how Ethereum used to work and

00:05:18.360 --> 00:05:21.401
what largely broke when we introduced

00:05:21.521 --> 00:05:22.062
L-Tools.

00:05:22.343 --> 00:05:24.543
We used to have one zone with Legos

00:05:24.583 --> 00:05:25.983
and anyone could build

00:05:26.665 --> 00:05:28.666
um, on top of other people's Legos.

00:05:29.226 --> 00:05:29.307
Um,

00:05:29.447 --> 00:05:31.228
and then we had different buckets and kind

00:05:31.249 --> 00:05:31.329
of,

00:05:31.348 --> 00:05:33.370
they all had Legos in themselves and they

00:05:33.509 --> 00:05:34.790
kind of had all had kind of like

00:05:34.930 --> 00:05:36.952
Lego landscapes that kind of work in and

00:05:36.992 --> 00:05:37.593
of themselves.

00:05:38.194 --> 00:05:39.574
Um, but, um,

00:05:40.312 --> 00:05:44.396
building with different pieces in

00:05:44.456 --> 00:05:46.617
different DAGO zones was impossible.

00:05:47.017 --> 00:05:50.281
And this has very much changed with the

00:05:50.480 --> 00:05:51.982
advances of real-time proofing.

00:05:52.041 --> 00:05:54.944
So now we can actually prove the state

00:05:55.464 --> 00:05:57.786
of another chain to any other chain,

00:05:58.067 --> 00:05:59.588
more or less in real time.

00:06:00.567 --> 00:06:06.812
So that chain can use that state as

00:06:07.533 --> 00:06:09.154
an input for its computation.

00:06:09.706 --> 00:06:12.127
Because any one network has a complete

00:06:12.208 --> 00:06:13.408
understanding of its own state.

00:06:13.788 --> 00:06:16.009
But understanding the other network state

00:06:16.088 --> 00:06:17.588
is always kind of where the trouble comes

00:06:17.608 --> 00:06:18.069
in.

00:06:18.588 --> 00:06:19.350
Until recently,

00:06:20.290 --> 00:06:23.310
proving the state of another network was

00:06:23.870 --> 00:06:24.250
stupid.

00:06:25.011 --> 00:06:26.031
So you could compose,

00:06:26.172 --> 00:06:27.451
but you couldn't do it synchronously.

00:06:27.531 --> 00:06:29.853
And kind of this is the composability is

00:06:29.913 --> 00:06:31.612
where the magic comes back.

00:06:32.533 --> 00:06:34.374
And if you have that feeling again that

00:06:35.392 --> 00:06:38.858
you have different protocols that can now

00:06:39.139 --> 00:06:41.040
very well sit on different parts of the

00:06:41.141 --> 00:06:42.442
EUT in different networks,

00:06:42.824 --> 00:06:46.309
but that can still plug into each other

00:06:46.389 --> 00:06:50.894
as seamlessly as we used to before we

00:06:50.975 --> 00:06:51.817
actually got L-tools.

