kind of the L-two and adjacent ecosystems

00:49:22.922 --> 00:49:25.764
that we'll need are ecosystems that

00:49:25.864 --> 00:49:28.005
complement L-two,

00:49:28.105 --> 00:49:30.266
not ecosystems that just replicate

00:49:30.784 --> 00:49:32.744
the same value proposition that kind of

00:49:33.585 --> 00:49:35.106
Ethereum already fulfills.

00:49:35.985 --> 00:49:41.547
So kind of stage two L-tos,

00:49:43.768 --> 00:49:50.128
they were quite restricted in kind of the

00:49:50.268 --> 00:49:53.769
user experience that they offered to dApp

00:49:53.809 --> 00:49:55.730
developers building on top of them.

00:49:56.449 --> 00:49:58.530
And the Ethereum Economic Zone

00:50:00.275 --> 00:50:04.778
basically now allows all kinds of roll ups

00:50:04.858 --> 00:50:06.880
and technically you don't even have to be

00:50:06.900 --> 00:50:08.702
a roll up to kind of join the

00:50:08.742 --> 00:50:09.342
economic zone.

00:50:09.762 --> 00:50:11.023
And I think that's the beauty of it.

00:50:11.103 --> 00:50:14.505
So it's maximally permissive in terms of

00:50:17.199 --> 00:50:18.501
who can partake.

00:50:18.601 --> 00:50:20.601
It's not opinionated.

00:50:21.981 --> 00:50:24.603
It's open source software.

00:50:24.623 --> 00:50:25.742
It belongs to everyone.

00:50:25.802 --> 00:50:27.083
It should belong to everyone.

00:50:27.523 --> 00:50:33.947
And I think that's going to be what

00:50:34.007 --> 00:50:37.867
will ensure that this is the architecture

00:50:38.047 --> 00:50:39.568
that we will see for Ethereum in the

00:50:39.608 --> 00:50:39.849
future.

